title: Boston United 2-2 Woking
title_page: Boston United 2-2 Woking: Match report - BBC Sport
maintext:
Jai Rowe scored a stoppage-time equaliser as relegation-threatened Boston snatched a 2-2 draw with Woking in the National League.
Rowe bundled home his second of the game at the Jakemans Community Stadium as the Pilgrims came from behind for a second time.
The hosts had started well with Frankie Maguire having an effort tipped onto the bar but Harry Beautyman fired Woking ahead after 23 minutes.
Rowe rewarded Boston for a strong spell of pressure when he headed them level on 66 minutes and he needed to produce another rescue act after Inih Effiong put Woking back ahead 14 minutes from time.
